http://www.w3.org/2003/01/geo/wgs84_pos#.name: SpatialThing
http://www.w3.org/2003/01/geo/wgs84_pos#.description:
Anything with spatial extent, i.e. size, shape, or position.
 e.g. people, places, bowling balls, as well as abstract areas like cubes.

http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/Agent.name: Agent
http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/Agent.description: An agent (eg. person, group, software or physical artifact).

http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/LabelProperty.name: LabelProperty
http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/LabelProperty.description: A foaf:LabelProperty is any RDF property with texual values that serve as labels.

http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/Project.name: Project
http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/Project.description: A project (a collective endeavour of some kind).

http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-.name: foaf_Type
http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-.description: The subject is an instance of a class.

http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-.name: foaf_Value
http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-.description: Idiomatic property used for structured values.

http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#com.name: rdfs_Comment
http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#com.description: A description of the subject resource.

http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isD.name: rdfs_IsDefinedBy
http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isD.description: The definition of the subject resource.

http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#lab.name: rdfs_Label
http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#lab.description: A human-readable name for the subject.

http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#mem.name: rdfs_Member
http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#mem.description: A member of the subject resource.

http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#see.name: rdfs_SeeAlso
http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#see.description: Further information about the subject resource.

http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#sub.name: rdfs_SubClassOf
http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#sub.description: The subject is a subclass of a class.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#annotatedP.name: owl_AnnotatedProperty
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#annotatedP.description: The property that determines the predicate of an annotated axiom or annotated annotation.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#annotatedS.name: owl_AnnotatedSource
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#annotatedS.description: The property that determines the subject of an annotated axiom or annotated annotation.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#annotatedT.name: owl_AnnotatedTarget
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#annotatedT.description: The property that determines the object of an annotated axiom or annotated annotation.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#bottomData.name: owl_BottomDataProperty
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#bottomData.description: The data property that does not relate any individual to any data value.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#bottomObje.name: owl_BottomObjectProperty
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#bottomObje.description: The object property that does not relate any two individuals.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#deprecated.name: owl_Deprecated
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#deprecated.description: The annotation property that indicates that a given entity has been deprecated.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#differentF.name: owl_DifferentFrom
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#differentF.description: The property that determines that two given individuals are different.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#equivalent.name: owl_EquivalentClass
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#equivalent.description: The property that determines that two given classes are equivalent, and that is used to specify datatype definitions.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#intersecti.name: owl_IntersectionOf
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#intersecti.description: The property that determines the collection of classes or data ranges that build an intersection.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#members.name: owl_Members
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#members.description: The property that determines the collection of members in either a owl:AllDifferent, owl:AllDisjointClasses or owl:AllDisjointProperties axiom.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#oneOf.name: owl_OneOf
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#oneOf.description: The property that determines the collection of individuals or data values that build an enumeration.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#sameAs.name: owl_SameAs
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#sameAs.description: The property that determines that two given individuals are equal.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#topDataPro.name: owl_TopDataProperty
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#topDataPro.description: The data property that relates every individual to every data value.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#topObjectP.name: owl_TopObjectProperty
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#topObjectP.description: The object property that relates every two individuals.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#unionOf.name: owl_UnionOf
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#unionOf.description: The property that determines the collection of classes or data ranges that build a union.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#versionInf.name: owl_VersionInfo
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#versionInf.description: The annotation property that provides version information for an ontology or another OWL construct.

http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/account.name: account
http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/account.description: Indicates an account held by this agent.

http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/accountName.name: accountName
http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/accountName.description: Indicates the name (identifier) associated with this online account.

http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/accountService.name: accountServiceHomepage
http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/accountService.description: Indicates a homepage of the service provide for this online account.

http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/age.name: age
http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/age.description: The age in years of some agent.

http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/based_near.name: basedNear
http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/based_near.description: A location that something is based near, for some broadly human notion of near.

http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/birthday.name: birthday
http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/birthday.description: The birthday of this Agent, represented in mm-dd string form, eg. '12-31'.

http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/currentProject.name: currentProject
http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/currentProject.description: A current project this person works on.

http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/depicts.name: depicts
http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/depicts.description: A thing depicted in this representation.

http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/familyName.name: familyName
http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/familyName.description: The family name of some person.

http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/family_name.name: familyName1
http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/family_name.description: The family name of some person.

http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/firstName.name: firstName
http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/firstName.description: The first name of a person.

http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/fundedBy.name: fundedBy
http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/fundedBy.description: An organization funding a project or person.

http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/geekcode.name: geekcode
http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/geekcode.description: A textual geekcode for this person, see http://www.geekcode.com/geek.html

http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/gender.name: gender
http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/gender.description: The gender of this Agent (typically but not necessarily 'male' or 'female').

http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/holdsAccount.name: holdsAccount
http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/holdsAccount.description: Indicates an account held by this agent.

http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/img.name: image
http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/img.description: An image that can be used to represent some thing (ie. those depictions which are particularly representative of something, eg. one's photo on a homepage).

http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/interest.name: interest
http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/interest.description: A page about a topic of interest to this person.

http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/isPrimaryTopic.name: isPrimaryTopicOf
http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/isPrimaryTopic.description: A document that this thing is the primary topic of.

http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/knows.name: knows
http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/knows.description: A person known by this person (indicating some level of reciprocated interaction between the parties).

http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/lastName.name: lastName
http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/lastName.description: The last name of a person.

http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/made.name: made
http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/made.description: Something that was made by this agent.

http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/maker.name: maker
http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/maker.description: An agent that  made this thing.

http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/mbox.name: personalMailbox
http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/mbox.description: A  personal mailbox, ie. an Internet mailbox associated with exactly one owner, the first owner of this mailbox. This is a 'static inverse functional property', in that  there is (across time and change) at most one individual that ever has any particular value for foaf:mbox.

http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/mbox_sha1sum.name: sha1sumOfAPersonalMailboxURIName
http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/mbox_sha1sum.description: The sha1sum of the URI of an Internet mailbox associated with exactly one owner, the  first owner of the mailbox.

http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/member.name: member
http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/member.description: Indicates a member of a Group

http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/page.name: page
http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/page.description: A page or document about this thing.

http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/pastProject.name: pastProject
http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/pastProject.description: A project this person has previously worked on.

http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/plan.name: plan
http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/plan.description: A .plan comment, in the tradition of finger and '.plan' files.

http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/primaryTopic.name: primaryTopic
http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/primaryTopic.description: The primary topic of some page or document.

http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/publications.name: publications
http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/publications.description: A link to the publications of this person.

http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/schoolHomepage.name: schoolHomepage
http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/schoolHomepage.description: A homepage of a school attended by the person.

http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/status.name: status
http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/status.description: A string expressing what the user is happy for the general public (normally) to know about their current activity.

http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/tipjar.name: tipjar
http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/tipjar.description: A tipjar document for this agent, describing means for payment and reward.

http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/topic.name: topic
http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/topic.description: A topic of some page or document.

http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/topic_interest.name: topicInterest
http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/topic_interest.description: A thing of interest to this person.

http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/weblog.name: weblog
http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/weblog.description: A weblog of some thing (whether person, group, company etc.).

http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/workInfoHomepa.name: workInfoHomepage
http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/workInfoHomepa.description: A work info homepage of some person; a page about their work for some organization.

http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/workplaceHomep.name: workplaceHomepage
http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/workplaceHomep.description: A workplace homepage of some person; the homepage of an organization they work for.
